(607, '<![CDATA[<div class=\"col-sm-192 col-lg-192 col-md-192 col-xs-192 archive_banner\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"img-responsive zoom-img\" src=\"http://images.scdaarchitects.com/www_scdaarchitects_com/SCDA_Soo_K_Chan_Botanika_Singapore_073.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"628\" height=\"479\" data-enlarge=\"http://images.scdaarchitects.com/www_scdaarchitects_com/SCDA_Soo_K_Chan_Botanika_Singapore_070.jpg\" data-height=\"1080\" data-width=\"1417\" /></div>\n<div class=\"archive_intro\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>BOTANIKA</strong>  |  Singapore</p>\n<p>Inspired by the form, texture and palette of its context, Botanika evolved from an initial formal massing response to the site’s parameters to become a sensitive insertion in the existing landscape and fabric of the Holland Road area. Set amid a framework of mature rain trees, the site offers an opportunity to create a residential resort enclave, a place to retreat from the pace of urban life while enjoying close connections to the city.</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"col-sm-192 col-lg-192 col-md-192 col-xs-192 archive_banner\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"img-responsive zoom-img\" src=\"http://images.scdaarchitects.com/www_scdaarchitects_com/SCDA_Soo_K_Chan_Botanika_Singapore_031.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"630\" height=\"330\" data-enlarge=\"http://images.scdaarchitects.com/www_scdaarchitects_com/SCDA_Soo_K_Chan_Botanika_Singapore_030.jpg\" data-height=\"859\" data-width=\"1919\" /></div>\n<div class=\"col-sm-192 col-lg-192 col-md-192 col-xs-192 archive_banner\">\n<div class=\"col-sm-118 col-lg-118 col-md-118 col-xs-118\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"img-responsive zoom-img\" src=\"http://images.scdaarchitects.com/www_scdaarchitects_com/SCDA_Soo_K_Chan_Botanika_Singapore_11.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"390\" height=\"332\" data-enlarge=\"http://images.scdaarchitects.com/www_scdaarchitects_com/SCDA_Soo_K_Chan_Botanika_Singapore_10.jpg\" data-height=\"1080\" data-width=\"1742\" /></div>\n<div class=\"col-sm-74 col-lg-74 col-md-74 col-x