(1091, 'LAKESHORE VIEW HOUSE', '', 0, 0, 1071),
(1092, 'Located at the highest hillside parcel overlooking the nearby Golf Course and the port shoreline, Lakeshore View House addresses the potential of a sloping site using a composition of volumes that addresses the Owner’s brief whilst creating a flow of formal and informal interconnected spaces.', '', 0, 0, 1072),
(1093, 'Fit within the contours of the site, the house is viewed modestly from arrival, creating a sense of expectation upon approach. A series of terraced watercourts unifies space through the heart of the building on its central axis, flowing from a quiet reflective pond on the upper levels down through stepped landscaping to drop further to the poolside level where a panoramic viewing deck lines the length of a cantilevered acrylic edged swimming pool.', '', 0, 0, 1073),
(1094, 'Thu, 27 Aug 2020 08:50:16 +0000', '', 0, 0, 1074),
