(717, 'This house at Bishopsgate Road is an elegant dialectic of monolithic and delicate architectural elements. Overall, the expression of the house is a response to the client’s affinity for modern art. Purity is the order of the day and the entire composition forms an unadulterated and clean landscape that provides an ideal backdrop for the client’s personal collection of sculptural art.'),
