(945, 'DHOBY GHAUT GREEN'),
(946, 'As part of Singapore’s Urban Redevelopment Authority’s plan to increase the number of public spaces in the Orchard Road area, this park is envisioned as a wonderful ‘living room’, a gathering space where people can come together to enjoy a performance. While designed for major events and celebrations, the space also encourages informal gatherings on non-event days, offering respite for those who seek an alternative or quiet space in the heart of the city.'),
